CAMPAIGN_NAME: Trace element levels in harp seal and hooded seal from Greenland Sea study
ORGANISATION: Institute of Nutrition, Directorate of Fisheries
CAMPAIGN_COMMENT: Muscle, liver and kidney were sampled from 29 harp seals (6 juveniles, 8 males and 15 females) and 22 hooded seals (2 juveniles, 5 males and 15 females) captured in the Greenland Sea by research scientists from the Marine Research Institute, Bergen in the winter season of 1985.
